fields.label: AcademicQualification
fields.comment: An academic achievement that is officially recognized.

fields.label: AccountingAccount
fields.comment: A specific trade account for recording debits and credits to general accounting, cost accounting or budget accounting.

fields.label: Accreditation
fields.comment: A certified recognition that provides evidence of a level of competency in a given area, such as certifying a level of skill in a trade.

fields.label: AcknowledgementDocument
fields.comment: A document exchanged between parties for a business application level acknowledgement of the receipt of information.

fields.label: Address
fields.comment: The location at which a particular trade related organization or person may be found or reached.

fields.label: AdvancePayment
fields.comment: A prepaid discharge of obligations in respect of funds or securities transferred between two or more parties.

fields.label: AgriculturalApplication
fields.comment: Any substance such as seed, fertilizer, water, gas or chemical applied to an agricultural field, substrate, construction, plant, animal or product.

fields.label: AgriculturalCertificate
fields.comment: A legal proof of ownership, worthiness or qualification to operate an agricultural item.

fields.label: AgriculturalCharacteristic
fields.comment: A prominent attribute or aspect of an agricultural object.

fields.label: AgriculturalProcess
fields.comment: A practice of cultivating land, raising crops, or treatment of the agricultural produce.

fields.label: Allergy
fields.comment: A guest condition of the abnormal reaction of the body to a previously encountered substance introduced by inhalation, ingestion, injection, or skin contact.

fields.label: AnimalBatch
fields.comment: A group of animals dealt with together.

fields.label: AnimalCertificate
fields.comment: A collection of data for a piece of written, printed or electronic matter that provides information or evidence about the identity of an animal or a batch of animals.

fields.label: AnimalCertification
fields.comment: The process of certifying that a certain animal has met performance and quality assurance requirements, or qualification requirements as stipulated in regulations.

fields.label: AnimalHoldingEvent
fields.comment: The keeping of an animal in a particular location.

fields.label: AnimalIdentity
fields.comment: Information about an animal which uniquely identifies it.

fields.label: AppliedAllowanceCharge
fields.comment: The applied allowance or charge component of pricing.

fields.label: AppliedChemicalTreatment
fields.comment: A process of applying a chemical, physical, or biological agent to an object.

fields.label: AppliedTax
fields.comment: A total levy or payment for the support of a government that is required of persons, groups, or businesses within the domain of that government.

fields.label: Area
fields.comment: A named, delimited and identified part of a land and or water surface of the globe subject to dedicated uniform agricultural treatment.

fields.label: Assertion
fields.comment: A statement that user needs of the present are met without compromising the needs of future generations.

fields.label: Assessment
fields.comment: The evaluation of an object, such as a product, process, or organization, with respect to the object's worth or condition.

fields.label: Authentication
fields.comment: A proof that a document is genuine.

fields.label: AuthoritativeSignatoryPerson
fields.comment: A person who is authorized to sign a document, such as a customs officer or other government official.

fields.label: AvailablePeriod
fields.comment: A specific period of time such as the length of time between two known date/time points, from a start date onwards, or up to an end date for which something is available.

fields.label: BinaryFile
fields.comment: A specified computer file or program stored in a binary format.

fields.label: Booking
fields.comment: A result of a financial transaction recorded within a financial account.

fields.label: BotanicalCrop
fields.comment: Plants or produce cultivated from a single botanical species or variety.

fields.label: BranchFinancialInstitution
fields.comment: A sub-division of a bank, building society, credit union, stock brokerage, or similar business; established primarily to provide financial services and financial transactions.

fields.label: BreakdownStatement
fields.comment: A detailed statement of work, prices, and dimensions for this valuation.

fields.label: CalculatedPrice
fields.comment: Information related to a calculated price.

fields.label: CalibratedMeasurement
fields.comment: A measurement established by a device which is tested to a calibration standard of known accuracy.

fields.label: CancellationStatus
fields.comment: Information relevant to a condition of a cancellation.

fields.label: Cargo
fields.comment: Information about goods being transported identifying their nature for customs, statistical or transport purposes.

fields.label: CargoInsurance
fields.comment: Insurance coverage for cargo during transport movements.

fields.label: CarriedEquipment
fields.comment: A tool or device carried by a guest for an activity.

fields.label: Cash
fields.comment: Coins, banknotes paid by the recipient of goods or services to the provider.

fields.label: Chemical
fields.comment: Any clearly defined substance having a defined molecular composition.

fields.label: Cheque
fields.comment: A written payment order to a bank to pay the stated sum from the drawer's account.

fields.label: Circle
fields.comment: A planar surface specified as one completely round flat shape in the mathematical sense.

fields.label: Classification
fields.comment: A systematic arrangement of products in classes or categories according to established criteria.

fields.label: Clause
fields.comment: A distinct article or provision in a document, which requires compliance.

fields.label: Communication
fields.comment: The exchange of thoughts, messages, or information, as universally exchanged by speech, signals, writing, or behaviour between persons and/or organizations.

fields.label: ComplexDescription
fields.comment: An aggregation of descriptive information consisting of different but related characteristics that together constitute a work item complex description.

fields.label: ConformanceCertificate
fields.comment: The label delivered by a trusted third party to assess the compliance of a product or a service with an agreed standard.

fields.label: Consignment
fields.comment: A separately identifiable collection of goods items to be transported or available to be transported from one consignor to one consignee in a supply chain via one or more modes of transport where each consignment is the subject of one single transport contract.,A referenced, separately identifiable collection of goods items to be transported or available to be transported from one consignor to one consignee via one or more modes of transport where each consignment is the subject of one single transport contract.

fields.label: ConsignmentItem
fields.comment: A reference to an item within a supply chain consignment of goods separately identified for transport and customs purposes.,An item within a supply chain consignment of goods separately identified for transport and customs purposes.

fields.label: Contract
fields.comment: An agreement between two or more parties for trade purposes.

fields.label: ControlSettingParameter
fields.comment: A set of measurable factors that specifies the conditions of its operation within a specific context.

fields.label: Convoy
fields.comment: A number of means of transport following each other with a common logistics purpose.

fields.label: CooperatingOrganization
fields.comment: An organized structure set up for a particular purpose, such as a business, government body, department, charity, or financial institution that is working together with another organization, business, or person.

fields.label: CoordinateReferenceSystem
fields.comment: A coordinate reference system that is used in a contextually local sense to describe the relative locations of objects in which coordinates of points are recorded in a Coordinate System (CS) (reference ISO 19111).

fields.label: CoordinateSourceSystem
fields.comment: Properties defining a geographical coordinate source system used in different places around the world to identify locations on the earth.

fields.label: CorrectiveAction
fields.comment: Improvements taken to eliminate causes of non-conformities or other undesirable situations, such as to an organization's processes or products.

fields.label: CorrectiveEvent
fields.comment: An occurrence or happening related to an object or process that is subject to a correction.

fields.label: Country
fields.comment: The area of land that belongs to a nation together with its properties, such as population, political organization, etc., used or referenced for trade purposes.

fields.label: CountrySubDivision
fields.comment: A political or physical area or region within the political boundaries of a country used or referenced for trade purposes.

fields.label: CreditorFinancialAccount
fields.comment: A specific business arrangement whereby credits arising from transactions are recorded.

fields.label: CreditorFinancialInstitution
fields.comment: A bank, building society, credit union, stock brokerage, or similar business of the party that receives money.

fields.label: CropMixtureConstituent
fields.comment: A plant species or variety constituting part of a field crop mixture.

fields.label: CropProduceBatch
fields.comment: A group of crop produce considered or dealt with together.

fields.label: CropProtectionTreatment
fields.comment: A method or substance, such as chemical fertilizers and crop protection products, applied to plant growth whilst managing and controlling diseases and pests.

fields.label: CurrencyExchange
fields.comment: The conversion of one currency to another for trade purposes.

fields.label: CustomerClass
fields.comment: The conditions and requirements of the type of person who may use or purchase a product or service.

fields.label: CustomsValuation
fields.comment: A cross-border trade related assessment of the worth of an object, such as its monetary value, for customs purposes.

fields.label: DangerousGoods
fields.comment: Goods which may contain a substance which poses risks to people and/or the environment during transportation which is regulated by dangerous goods regulations.

fields.label: DebtorFinancialAccount
fields.comment: A specific business arrangement whereby debits arising from transactions are recorded.

fields.label: DebtorFinancialInstitution
fields.comment: A bank, building society, credit union, stock brokerage, or similar business of the party that owes money.

fields.label: DelimitedPeriod
fields.comment: A period of time from a start date time onwards up to an end date time.

fields.label: DeliveryAdjustment
fields.comment: A correction or modification to reflect actual delivery conditions.

fields.label: DeliveryInstructions
fields.comment: Delivery information of an instructive nature.

fields.label: DeliverySchedule
fields.comment: Specification of the forecasted delivery quantities and date/time values for a delivery schedule.

fields.label: DeliveryTerms
fields.comment: Conditions agreed upon between the parties with regard to the delivery of goods and or services for trade purposes.

fields.label: DigitalMethod
fields.comment: The use of online and digital technologies to collect monetary payment amounts.

fields.label: DirectPosition
fields.comment: A specified physical location described within a coordinate reference system.

fields.label: DirectPositionList
fields.comment: The specified list of coordinates for a physical location, expressed as a sequence of direct positions.

fields.label: Disability
fields.comment: A physical or mental condition that limits a guest's movements, senses, or activities.

fields.label: DisposalInstructions
fields.comment: A set of instructions detailing how to properly dispose of a material.

fields.label: Document
fields.comment: Written, printed or electronic matter that is referenced.

fields.label: DocumentCharacteristic
fields.comment: A prominent attribute or aspect of a document.

fields.label: DocumentContextParameter
fields.comment: A feature that is fixed for a particular document context.

fields.label: DocumentHandlingInstructions
fields.comment: Instructions for handling the document, such as stamping the agent signature.

fields.label: DocumentLineDocument
fields.comment: A collection of data for a line on a piece of written, printed or electronic matter that provides information or evidence.

fields.label: DocumentStatus
fields.comment: The information relevant to a condition related to a document.

fields.label: Emission
fields.comment: A calculation of the pollution (including noise, heat, and radiation etc.) discharged into the environment by a residential, commercial, or industrial facility or by a means of transport, such as a vessel, aircraft or truck.

fields.label: EmployerIdentity
fields.comment: Identification of a party who pays someone to do work on a regular or contractual basis.

fields.label: Equipment
fields.comment: Hardware or software typically marketed by a company other than the original manufacturer.

fields.label: Error
fields.comment: A notification that an error has occurred.

fields.label: Event
fields.comment: A significant occurrence or happening during transport.,A referenced significant occurrence or happening during transport.

fields.label: EventElement
fields.comment: Information about an event in which a Track and Trace (TT) element of one of more physical or digital objects is identified by a specific object class identifier (such as an electronic product class), either a specific quantity or an unspecified quantity.

fields.label: ExchangedDeclaration
fields.comment: A collection of data for a piece of written, printed or electronic matter that is exchanged between two parties as a formal declaration.

fields.label: ExchangedDocument
fields.comment: A collection of data for a piece of written, printed or electronic matter that is exchanged between two or more parties.

fields.label: ExchangedDocumentContext
fields.comment: The scenario or setting of an exchanged document, such as its business process application context.

fields.label: ExperienceEvent
fields.comment: An involvement in an experience program in which some thing happens, such as a nature watching, woodware manufacturing, meditation, holiday trip, dinner, theme park visit, could be experienced.

fields.label: ExperienceFacility
fields.comment: A structure or place, such as a restaurant, hotel, theme park, hot spring bathing pool, parking lot, or meeting room, that provides a particular experience.

fields.label: ExperienceItem
fields.comment: A collection of information specific to the involvement of a person or persons in a happening, such as a theme park, a guided tour being used or reported on for trade purposes.

fields.label: ExperienceProduct
fields.comment: Any service that provides an involvement, such as an adventure experience, wellness experience, social or business activity experience.

fields.label: ExperienceProgramAction
fields.comment: Any type of action, such as searching, reserving, or paying, necessary for an experience program, such as an adventure experience, a business experience, or a wellness experience.

fields.label: FieldCrop
fields.comment: A field with one or more cultivated plants or produce from one or more botanical species or varieties.

fields.label: FinancialAdjustment
fields.comment: A correction or modification to reflect actual financial conditions.

fields.label: FinancialCard
fields.comment: A card used to represent a financial account for a trade settlement.

fields.label: FinancialIdentity
fields.comment: A financial identification for an organization.

fields.label: FinancialInstitutionAddress
fields.comment: The location at which a financial institution may be found or reached.

fields.label: FinancingFinancialAccount
fields.comment: A financial account used internally by a bank to manage the line of credit granted to financing requesting party.

fields.label: FinancingRequestDocument
fields.comment: The set of characteristics shared by all individual transactions grouped for this financing request document.

fields.label: FinancingRequestResultDocument
fields.comment: A collection of data that reports the result of a financing request.

fields.label: FinancingStatus
fields.comment: Information relevant to a condition of financing.

fields.label: FinancingSummaryDocument
fields.comment: A collection of financing related data that provides an overview of key points.

fields.label: FoodChoice
fields.comment: A guest's decision which food to buy or eat.

fields.label: ForecastTerms
fields.comment: A set of terms and conditions by which a supply chain forecast has been or will be made.

fields.label: GeographicalCoordinate
fields.comment: A set of geographical coordinates of a specific point such as the longitude, latitude and altitude.

fields.label: GeographicalFeature
fields.comment: Representation of real world phenomenon associated with a location relative to the Earth, such as cities, buildings, roads, rivers, forests and lakes.

fields.label: GeographicalGrid
fields.comment: The combination of the latitude and longitude forming a graticule, used for specifying the position of any location on the surface of the Earth, without consideration of altitude or depth (reference ISO 19136).

fields.label: GeographicalLine
fields.comment: A connection between two points on the surface of the Earth (reference ISO 19136).

fields.label: GeographicalMultiCurve
fields.comment: A collection of curves on the surface of the Earth (reference ISO 19136).

fields.label: GeographicalMultiPoint
fields.comment: A collection of points, on the surface of the Earth (reference ISO 19136).

fields.label: GeographicalMultiSurface
fields.comment: A collection of surfaces on the Earth (reference ISO 19136).

fields.label: GeographicalObjectCharacteristic
fields.comment: An attribute of a geographical object.

fields.label: GeographicalPoint
fields.comment: A point on the surface of the Earth (reference ISO 19136).

fields.label: GeographicalSurface
fields.comment: A figure on the Earth having only two dimensions (reference ISO 19136).

fields.label: GeopoliticalRegion
fields.comment: A collection of countries and/or economies united for trade purposes.

fields.label: GoodsCharacteristic
fields.comment: A distinctive feature of a material contained within physical goods.

fields.label: GovernmentRegistration
fields.comment: The recording of items or details for a governmental purpose.

fields.label: GroupedWorkItem
fields.comment: A grouping of related work items.

fields.label: Guarantee
fields.comment: An official promise or assurance to fulfil a financial obligation.

fields.label: GuestArrival
fields.comment: The act of coming to or reaching a place by a specified guest.

fields.label: GuestHealthIndication
fields.comment: A guest's physical or mental condition.

fields.label: HandlingInstructions
fields.comment: Handling information of an instructive nature.

fields.label: HaulageInstructions
fields.comment: Instructions related to the action or process of conveyance.

fields.label: HazardousMaterial
fields.comment: Material which exhibits adverse effects on living organisms.

fields.label: HeaderBalanceOut
fields.comment: Offset header information to ensure that debits and credits are equal for a transaction.

fields.label: HeaderTradeAgreement
fields.comment: The contractual terms of a header trade agreement.

fields.label: HeaderTradeDelivery
fields.comment: Shipping arrangements and movement of products and or services including despatch and delivery at a header level.

fields.label: HeaderTradeSettlement
fields.comment: The information, at a header level, that enables the reconciliation of a financial transaction, with the item(s) that the financial transaction is intended to settle, such as a commercial invoice.

fields.label: IOTDevice
fields.comment: An IOT (Internet of Things) piece of mechanical or electronic equipment which can collect, report and autonomously transmit digital data.

fields.label: Illness
fields.comment: A WHO MDH (Maritime Declaration of Health) reported illness or disease for an onboard person.

fields.label: IndividualTTAnimal
fields.comment: A Track and Trace (TT) animal, such as one kept or raised on a farm, ranch.

fields.label: InformationSource
fields.comment: A person, organization, thing or place from which information comes, arises or is obtained.

fields.label: IngredientRangeMeasurement
fields.comment: A measurement of the variation limits of an ingredient.

fields.label: InspectionEvent
fields.comment: A significant occurrence or happening related to an inspection.

fields.label: InspectionInstructions
fields.comment: Information of an instructive nature that describes how to conduct an inspection.

fields.label: InspectionNote
fields.comment: Notes, such as conclusions, related to an inspection.

fields.label: InspectionPerson
fields.comment: An individual human being who conducts an inspection.

fields.label: InspectionReference
fields.comment: The identification of related information for an inspection.

fields.label: InspectionResult
fields.comment: Results obtained by performing an inspection.

fields.label: InspectionResultCharacteristic
fields.comment: A property of a collection of diagnostic data, visual or technical data, obtained by a performed inspection.

fields.label: InspectionStatus
fields.comment: The information relevant to a condition related to an inspection.

fields.label: InstalmentPayment
fields.comment: A discharge of obligations in respect of funds or securities, transferred through one of several payments, between two or more parties.

fields.label: InstalmentPlan
fields.comment: A plan for paying a total sum of money by several payments made over a period of time.

fields.label: InstructedTemperature
fields.comment: Temperature settings instructed for storage or movement of goods.

fields.label: Issue
fields.comment: A targeted topic for debate or resolution.

fields.label: Keyword
fields.comment: A significant word, part of word or phrase that is used to enable indexing of or searching within a textual repository, such as a product catalogue or library.

fields.label: LaboratoryObservationAnalysisMethod
fields.comment: A defined way of performing laboratory observation analysis.

fields.label: LaboratoryObservationContact
fields.comment: A person or department that acts as a point of contact for laboratory observations.

fields.label: LaboratoryObservationInstructions
fields.comment: Information of an instructive nature that describes how to conduct this laboratory observation.

fields.label: LaboratoryObservationNote
fields.comment: Notes and conclusions related to a laboratory observation.

fields.label: LaboratoryObservationParty
fields.comment: An individual, group, or body having a role in laboratory observations.

fields.label: LaboratoryObservationReference
fields.comment: The direction to related information for this laboratory observation.

fields.label: LanguageProficiency
fields.comment: Skills in any principal method of human communication, consisting of words used in a structured and conventional way and conveyed by speech, writing, or gesture.

fields.label: LegalOrganization
fields.comment: An organization set up on a legal basis as a business, government body, department, charity, or financial institution.

fields.label: LegalRegistration
fields.comment: The recording of items or details for a specific legal purpose.

fields.label: Licence
fields.comment: A permit from an authority to own or use something, do a particular thing, or to conduct a trade.

fields.label: LineTradeAgreement
fields.comment: The contractual terms of a line trade agreement.

fields.label: LineTradeDelivery
fields.comment: Shipping arrangements and movement of products and or services including despatch and delivery at a line level.

fields.label: LineTradeSettlement
fields.comment: The information, at a line level, that enables the reconciliation of a financial transaction with the item(s) that the financial transaction is intended to settle, for example a commercial invoice.

fields.label: LineTradeTransaction
fields.comment: A group of trade line items, trade line agreement, trade line delivery and trade line settlement details.

fields.label: LinearRing
fields.comment: A specified array of points which define a closed loop which is not self intersecting.

fields.label: Location
fields.comment: A reference to a physical location or place.

fields.label: LocationParty
fields.comment: An individual, a group, or a body having a role related to a location.

fields.label: LogisticsLabel
fields.comment: A label used for identifying goods for logistics purposes, such as a barcode, a radio frequency tag or a Vehicle Identification Number (VIN).

fields.label: LogisticsLocation
fields.comment: A logistics related physical location or place.

fields.label: LogisticsPackaging
fields.comment: Any wrapping or containment, such as a box or a barrel, whether or not any goods are contained within.

fields.label: LogisticsStatus
fields.comment: The information relevant to a condition or a position related to logistics.

fields.label: LogisticsTransportEquipment
fields.comment: A piece of equipment used to hold, protect or secure cargo for logistics purposes.,A referenced piece of equipment used to hold, protect or secure cargo for logistics purposes.TBR: description update to excersize GitHub update

fields.label: LogisticsTransportMeans
fields.comment: The devices used to convey goods or other objects from place to place during logistics cargo movements.

fields.label: MDHHealthIndication
fields.comment: Information related to a specific transportation indication to be reported on a WHO MDH (Maritime Declaration of Health).

fields.label: Machine
fields.comment: An apparatus specified to be used to perform an activity to produce something.

fields.label: Marketplace
fields.comment: An actual or virtual place where buyers and sellers interact, directly or through intermediaries, to trade goods or services.

fields.label: Marking
fields.comment: An inscription, stamp or label on packaging, such as to indicate date, ownership, quality, manufacture or origin.

fields.label: Measurement
fields.comment: An amount, size, or extent as established by measuring.

fields.label: Membership
fields.comment: The state of belonging to a group, such as a club or trade association.

fields.label: MetricCharacteristic
fields.comment: A prominent attribute or aspect of a metric (a standard of measurement).

fields.label: NegotiationContext
fields.comment: The protocol and setting of a negotiation.

fields.label: NegotiationExchange
fields.comment: An offer exchanged between parties for an electronic negotiation.

fields.label: Note
fields.comment: A textual or coded description, such as a remark or additional information.

fields.label: Object
fields.comment: Anything that is visible or tangible, such as a product, process, or organization.

fields.label: Observation
fields.comment: A specified act or instance of viewing or noting a fact or occurrence for some scientific or other special purpose.

fields.label: ObservationObjectiveParameter
fields.comment: A feature that is fixed for the case in question but may be different in other cases for this observation objective.

fields.label: ObservationResult
fields.comment: A collection of diagnostic data, visual or technical, and processing data, performed on a sample.

fields.label: ObservationResultCharacteristic
fields.comment: Specifies the type of the performed observation and the acquired values of this observation on the sample.

fields.label: OperationalParameter
fields.comment: A set of measurable factors that specifies the conditions within which an entity operates correctly.

fields.label: OrganizationCharacteristic
fields.comment: A prominent attribute or aspect of an organization.

fields.label: OrganizationalCertificate
fields.comment: A piece of written, printed or electronic matter that provides information or evidence that an organization has met required organizational criteria.

fields.label: OrganizationalCertification
fields.comment: The process of certifying organizational performance or qualification requirements as stipulated in regulations.

fields.label: Package
fields.comment: A self-contained wrapping or container within which goods can be contained for logistics purposes, such as a box or a barrel which can be filled, partially filled or empty.,A referenced self-contained wrapping or container within which goods can be contained for logistics purposes.

fields.label: PackagingInstructions
fields.comment: Packaging information of an instructive nature.

fields.label: Pairing
fields.comment: The process by which two potentially communicating entities are linked.

fields.label: PaymentBalanceOut
fields.comment: Offset information to ensure that debits and credits are equal for a transaction.

fields.label: PaymentDiscountTerms
fields.comment: Trade terms and conditions by which a discount is or can be applied to a payable amount.

fields.label: PaymentFinancialAccount
fields.comment: A specific business arrangement whereby monetary values pertaining to payment, collected or paid, are recorded.

fields.label: PaymentFinancialInstitution
fields.comment: An institution that provides financial services and financial transactions for payment.

fields.label: PaymentMeans
fields.comment: The means by which a payment will be or has been made for trade settlement purposes.

fields.label: PaymentPenaltyTerms
fields.comment: Trade terms and conditions by which a penalty is or can be applied to a payable amount.

fields.label: PaymentTerms
fields.comment: Terms and conditions by which payment has been or will be made for trade purposes.

fields.label: PaymentTradeSettlement
fields.comment: The information that enables the reconciliation of a payment with the item(s) that the payment is intended to settle, for example a commercial invoice.

fields.label: Person
fields.comment: A transport related person, such as a member of a crew or a passenger.

fields.label: PersonalEffects
fields.comment: Specified privately owned articles for personal use by an individual.

fields.label: PetAnimal
fields.comment: A domestic or tamed animal that is kept for companionship or pleasure.

fields.label: Picture
fields.comment: A photograph or video still represented as a digital image for electronic sharing.

fields.label: Plot
fields.comment: A small piece of land or water used for a crop such as an agricultural or aquacultural crop.

fields.label: Policy
fields.comment: A plan of action agreed or chosen in order to obey rules or requests made by people in authority and designed to prevent and detect violations of applicable law, regulations, rules and ethical standards by employees, agents and others.

fields.label: Polygon
fields.comment: A planar surface, defined by one exterior boundary and zero or more interior boundaries. Each interior boundary defines a hole in the polygon.

fields.label: Preference
fields.comment: An involvement in a happening, such as a theme park, a guided tour that is liked or wanted more than another item.

fields.label: PreventiveAction
fields.comment: An adjustment, such as a change to an organization's processes or products, taken to prevent non-conformities or other undesirable situations, possibly as a result of a risk analysis.

fields.label: Print
fields.comment: Any text or pattern put on the surface of a product using a specific material such as dye.

fields.label: ProcessCertificate
fields.comment: A piece of written, printed or electronic matter that provides information or evidence that a process has met required criteria.

fields.label: ProcessCertification
fields.comment: The process of certifying that a process has met performance and quality assurance tests, or qualification requirements.

fields.label: ProcessCharacteristic
fields.comment: A prominent attribute or aspect of a process.

fields.label: ProcessWorkItem
fields.comment: A distinct operation or task that is part of a process.

fields.label: Produce
fields.comment: Agricultural plants or plant products grown and harvested, such as grain, fruit, vegetables, silage.

fields.label: Product
fields.comment: A reference to a product or service produced by human or mechanical effort or by a natural process for trading purposes.

fields.label: ProductBatch
fields.comment: A group of products considered or dealt with together.

fields.label: ProductBatchCertificate
fields.comment: A piece of written, printed or electronic matter that provides information or evidence that a product batch has met required criteria.

fields.label: ProductBatchCertification
fields.comment: The process of certifying that a certain product batch has passed performance and quality assurance tests, or qualification requirements stipulated in regulations.

fields.label: ProductBatchCharacteristic
fields.comment: A prominent attribute or aspect of a group of products considered or dealt with together.

fields.label: ProductCertificate
fields.comment: A collection of data for a piece of written, printed or electronic matter that provides information or evidence about the product.

fields.label: ProductCharacteristic
fields.comment: A prominent attribute or aspect of a product.

fields.label: ProductCharacteristicCondition
fields.comment: A state that applies to a product characteristic.

fields.label: ProductFinishingTreatment
fields.comment: Improving measures for manufactured components or products to meet end use requirements.

fields.label: ProductHandlingProcess
fields.comment: A naturally occurring or designed sequence of operations or events that create, transform, or touch a product, such as manufacturing, treating, packaging, and storing.

fields.label: ProductInstance
fields.comment: An individual trade product or batch of similar trade products produced by human or mechanical effort or by a natural process.

fields.label: ProductLabel
fields.comment: A label, such as a garment label or a radio frequency tag, used for identifying a product.

fields.label: Production
fields.comment: The making or manufacturing of goods, such as from components or raw materials.

fields.label: ProductionCycle
fields.comment: A series of activities associated with the processing of a product.

fields.label: ProductionDevice
fields.comment: An object, especially a piece of mechanical or electronic equipment, made or adapted in order to perform a production activity.

fields.label: ProductionFacility
fields.comment: A man made physical structure, such as a building, in which something is produced.

fields.label: ProductionProcess
fields.comment: A naturally occurring or designed sequence of operations or events in order to produce something.

fields.label: ProductionUnit
fields.comment: A defined set of production processes under the single management of a facility.

fields.label: ProductionWasteMaterial
fields.comment: Any materials unused and rejected as unwanted during a production process.

fields.label: ProductionWasteMaterialComponent
fields.comment: A production material component that is unused and rejected as unwanted.

fields.label: ProductionWasteRecoveryDisposalProcess
fields.comment: A process of either regaining waste substances in usable form, or of getting rid of waste substances resulting from production.

fields.label: Project
fields.comment: An endeavour carefully planned to achieve a procurement of goods, works and service.

fields.label: ProprietaryIdentity
fields.comment: Proprietary information which uniquely identifies a person or organization.

fields.label: ProtectionMeans
fields.comment: A way to protect something, such as human beings, animals or environment, from getting infected or becoming ill.

fields.label: QuantityAnalysis
